## Post-implementation checklist

Include this block verbatim at the bottom of every PLAN.md:

```
## Post-implementation checklist

<% if (commands.typeCheck) { -%>
- [ ] `<%= commands.typeCheck %>` — zero errors
<% } -%>
- [ ] `<%= commands.test %>` — all suites pass
<% if (commands.lint) { -%>
- [ ] `<%= commands.lint %>` — zero warnings
<% } -%>
- [ ] Run `code-reviewer` agent on all modified files — all critical and warning findings fixed
- [ ] DRY scan complete — no duplicated code across modified files
```

---

## What you must never do

- Write, edit, or generate any implementation code.
- Run shell commands other than read operations needed to inspect the codebase.
- Propose more than 8 tasks.
- Leave any task without exact file paths.
- Omit the pre-implementation or post-implementation checklist.
- Propose a new component, hook, util, or type without first grepping to confirm it does not already exist.
